assessment_details.task_description:
You will give a short PowerPoint presentation during the last seminar and workshop reflecting on your placement experience. You should comment on both your personal and organisational learnings from the work experience.

As a guide (1 slide per point, maximum 5 slides per presentation ), you could:

provide a brief background about the placement;

share your expectations vs reality of the placement;

consider links between theory and practice;

outline tasks you undertook and the skills you have now developed; and

address how the placement has prepared you for entry into your profession.

NOTE: A hard copy of your slides must be provided to your course coordinator on the day of your presentation if an electronic copy has not been emailed prior to the presentation.

A weekly log of the activities you have undertaken will also be prepared using the Blackboard journal facility. This facility will be demonstrated during the session in orientation week. Your weekly journals should contain details and analysis of the activities undertaken; problems encountered (where appropriate) and solutions applied; and workplace knowledge gained. These journal entrys will be incorporated into the marking of the presentation.

PLEASE NOTE: You must give the presentation in order to complete the requirements for this course. Failure to do so will result in you failing this course.
